<br>
Has anyone played with the thought of getting a dedicated KCoG cleric a res stick?<br>
<br>
I just read that there's a new rule in with the KGC for Naggy/Ragefire, it goes something like, &quot;if you are camping Ragefire, you have to yeild your spot to the naggy raiding guild.&quot; Meaning if you are there to take down Naggy, you have the option of sticking around for the Ragefire spawn as well. (I think, correct me if I'm giddy)<br>
<br>
This would make at least obtaining an epic by the KCoG at least a possibility in the forseeable future.<br>
<br>
Of course being a cleric I'd die to get my hands on one of those things, but I think any cleric that hangs with the KCoG a lot is a good candidate for this. Just a couple &quot;things&quot; standing in the way...<br>
<br>
Ixiblat Fer - level 62, has 32,000 HPs, a gang of magicians are the way to go with him I've heard.<br>
<br>
Overking Bathezid - a level 65 Sarnak Wizard with 32,000 HPs, deep in Chardok, pain in the posterior probably. Probably has Greater Ice Comet or something.<br>
<br>
Ixiblat you have to hand in an item from the quest, so ya gotta be up to that point to make him spawn, and failure means starting over, but Overking can be done whenever. Then ya gotta do Ragefire, then ya got a cleric who can do reses whenever Sev is up.<br>
<br>
How hard could it be, I see these sticks everywhere. OK, totally off topic now, sorry. I'm easily exciteable, as I'm sure is every cleric reading this without their res stick yet. <p>-Lenenae McGillicuddy<br>
