<br>
Now, that being said, there's nothing wrong in requesting CoG help with obtaining YOUR epic.  Indeed there's no reason why you cannot request to take the ragefire camp after CoG takes Naggy down next time.  Of course, you'd have to supply some o fhte raiders since anyone from CoG would be purely volunteers.  And if there are several clerics that want Rage I imagine you'd have to roll against them for the camp.  That'd be up to the Raid Leader tho.  <br>
<br>
So I dont see how CoG could manage to work through and get a cleric an epic.  We can, however, help with specific parts, you just need to lead those raids and post for volunteers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Difficulty.  Ix is fairly hardish.  I know SB recently took a crack at him so they'd know better.  The few times I went was with Forged Alliance and it was fairly simple once we got our coordination in.  Overking, once again fairly hardish.  Main thing is getting your raid together.  Although you might be able to combine that and Ix together.  Rage.  Er...good luck.  The camp is mind numbing, almost as bad as the old Faydadear, and CR is a pain.  Probably the hardest part, however, would be the Weight of the Earth (or whatever it is) from PoA.  Rare drop from the 4th island.  That's a 3 day raid, 8 hours a day, once your up, you cant come back down, same as hate takes a 250pp stone per group, need about 4-6 groups really.  Average expense is something around 600pp per person.  Generally only the larger alliances and guilds do this, so I'd advise making some friends with them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Rez sticks arent the hardest to get, but they're still pretty hard.  The reason you see so many is that most guilds/alliances will drop what they're doing to equip their clerics with them first.  Not only does it make good raid sense, it'll make all other epics easier to get as well.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Who's up for Fay?  Lol.<br>
<br>
And to clarify, the rule on the guild doing Naggy getting the Ragefire camp isnt really a new rule.  Its really just an extention of the whole concept of a camp.  Rage share's Naggy's spawn point so if Naggy is up, Rage simply cant spawn.  If a mob cannot spawn, you cannot camp it.  Hence, when Naggy appears/spawns whomever was camping Rage automaticlly loses the camp to the guild that comes in to kill Naggy.  Since that guild is already there on top of the spawn point, they get the camp next.  This is generally bad for the poor cleric who just lost their camp after spending 2 days sitting there.  But those are the breaks.  Often clerics will make other arrangements with the next guild coming in.  Most will be as accomodating as possible.  And rarely do fights break out, although it has been known to happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#8E9173>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds>Council of Guilds</a><font color=#8E9173> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8>CoG Dragon Raids</a> <font color=#8E9173> - </font><a href="http://members.fortunecity.com/haemish">Karana Council of Guilds</a><font color=#8E9173> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href=http://www.coolsavings.com/index.asp?Ref=ezboard&BN=link-groccouons&BL=groc>PRINT FREE GROCERY COUPONS AT CoolSavings. Click Here!</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><IMG SRC="http://service.bfast.com/bfast/serve?bfmid=7279965&siteid=33932331&bfpage=expertc_tax" BORDER="0" WIDTH="1" HEIGHT="1" NOSAVE >
